Instant gratification doesn't seem to be the person you want to control the steering wheel.
He lives completely in the moment.
He has no memories of the past, no knowledge of the future, he only cares about two things: simplicity and happiness.
In the animal world, this is not a problem.
If you are a dog, living a simple and happy life, you have already achieved great success!
As for the monkey, humans are another kind of animal.
Sleeping well, eating enough, and reproducing for the next generation may not be a problem in the tribal era.
However, if you haven't noticed, we are not living in the tribal era now.
We live in an advanced civilization, but the monkey has no idea what that is.
This is why we have another guy in our heads, the rational decision-maker, who enables us to do things that other animals cannot do.
We can foresee the future.
We can consider the overall situation.
We can make long-term plans.
And he wants to take all of these into consideration.
He wants us to do anything worth doing now.
Sometimes, doing simple and happy things is meaningful, such as eating, sleeping, or enjoying well-deserved leisure time.
